ad_creative_body: As Republicans, I’ve always felt we should emphasize the ‘conserve’ in conservative, and environmental concerns aside, I was elected to represent Charleston. We have a multi-BILLION dollar tourist economy, and these folks aren’t coming to see offshore drilling. They're coming for the Lowcountry's natural beauty, and that's why — less than a week into my legislative career — I kept my campaign promise to protect our precious coastline by filing an Anti-Offshore Resolution in the SC House of Representatives. I refiled this legislation earlier this year with a long list of bipartisan support in the House. Today, I remain committed in my opposition to offshore drilling and seismic testing in South Carolina's coastal waters. Are you with me?

I grew up in America’s Heartland. My grandfather was an iron ore miner, my father was a newspaperman and my mother was a proud school teacher and union member. 

Thanks to their hard work, I had the opportunity to become the first woman elected to the U.S. Senate from Minnesota -- and now I'm running for president to build a country where everyone, not just the lucky few, can succeed. But I need you with me: Sign on to join my campaign. http://bit.ly/2Zes3yS

ad_creative_body: Let me be crystal clear - I strongly oppose using your tax dollars to reduce the number of lanes on our roads. Anyone who thinks that taking lanes away from cars will “help improve the flow of traffic” should have their head examined. It’s terrifying that Democrats in Sacramento have let the inmates run the asylum, or in this case run the Dept. of Transportation. In D.C., I’m fighting to fund local projects to ADD capacity, like the 91W auxiliary lane at Green River and improving the 15 in Temecula.

ad_creative_body:
It was great seeing so many new faces, along with old friends like Eric Chapman (pictured). As always, I appreciated the opportunity to discuss the important issues facing our nation, to hear your feedback, and to answer your questions.  We have many successes to celebrate from the last year and a half – including historic tax relief, historically low unemployment, VA reforms, and a robust military budget. Much work remains to be done this year, and I hope to have your continued input and involvement.  None of these successes would have been possible without your support and involvement.

Once again, thank you to everyone who came out to join the conversation!

ad_creative_body:
I’m about to ask you to make a contribution to my campaign before this quarter’s fundraising deadline. Please give me a moment to explain why this is so important:

Your support has never been more critical than it is right now.

Before I even made the ballot, I faced unprecedented out-of-state special interest spending and attacks from right-wing groups. 

I’m sure that more nasty attacks are on there way and it would be devastating if these right-wing groups got away with twisting facts to attack my character and record.

Will you help make sure that doesn’t happen? Donate whatever you can today. Every bit helps.

ad_creative_body:
I’ll admit, I get frustrated when people make this whole election about Donald Trump. Iowa, can’t we believe in something bigger than that?

I’m running for president to repair the damage Trump has done and undo the hatred he’s sowed. But I’m also running to unite Americans in common purpose to ensure abundant opportunity in every community and justice that is real for everyone. Will you join me?

I was named the most effective Democratic Senator in the 115th Congress because I get things done. And as president, I’ll do the same from day 1. But I need you with me: Sign on to join my campaign. http://bit.ly/2ZeitvU

Some candidates have big-money fundraising down to a science: Swoop into a city, drive to a swanky hotel or hedge fund office, make pleasant chit-chat with the rich and powerful, and scoop up big checks. But not Elizabeth. She knows our movement depends on putting the voices of voters above corporations. She spends that time in selfie lines and talking to voters like you. But it’s only possible with your support.

Will you chip in now to help Elizabeth show the power of our grassroots movement before the FEC filing deadline on September 30th?

Voter rights are critical to a functional democracy. Here in Washington state, we are fortunate to have started voting by mail. We know it works, voting by mail:
- Breaks down barriers for seniors, working families, disabled Americans, and young voters.
- Uses unhackable paper ballots that can be recounted and audited by hand.
- Gives people the time and safety to vote from the convenience of their own home, allowing them to avoid long lines, limiting polling place hours, or the hassle of missing work.

As our country is confronted by the logistical challenges of the coronavirus pandemic, it has never been more urgent to expand this option nationwide. 

Sign the petition to implement vote-by-mail and protect our 2020 elections.

ad_creative_body:
It’s getting harder and harder for working families to save enough for retirement. But Congress hasn’t increased Social Security benefits in nearly fifty years. When Washington politicians discuss Social Security, it’s mostly to talk about cutting benefits by a lot or a little bit. After cutting taxes for the rich and big corporations, Donald Trump twice proposed cutting billions from Social Security. 

We need to get our priorities straight. We need to be increasing Society Security benefits and asking the richest Americans to contribute their fair share to the program. That’s why I’m announcing my plan to provide the biggest and most progressive increase in Social Security benefits in almost 50 years.

My plan increases Social Security benefits immediately by $200 a month — $2,400 a year –– for every current and future Social Security beneficiary in America. If you aren’t getting Social Security benefits now but will someday, your monthly benefit check with be at least $200 bigger than it otherwise would have been. 

I will also update outdated rules to further increase benefits for lower-income families, women, people with disabilities, public-sector workers, and people of color. We’ll pay for these changes and extend the solvency of Social Security by nearly 20 years by asking the richest 2% of families to contribute their fair share to the program. 

My plan will immediately lift an estimated 4.9 million seniors out of poverty, cutting the senior poverty rate by 68%. Seniors today are already facing a difficult retirement. Without action today, future generations are likely to be even worse off. 

It’s time Washington stopped trying to slash Social Security benefits instea. If you’re ready to fight tdo expand Social Security benefits for people who’ve earned them, sign up now to join our fight.

ad_creative_body:
I'm in Tolland, speaking to folks about my Business Plan to hold Hartford accountable as your next Republican Comptroller.

For too long, the State Comptroller has been a rubber stamp for Hartford's reckless spending, taxes and debt. I'm a business leader and a political outsider. I'll re-open Connecticut to business and balance our budgets. And here is my plan to do it:

1.) I'll launch a top-to-bottom audit of all government spending. 

2.) I'll lead by example by refusing a pension.

3.) I'll vote NO against any more excessive borrowing on the State Bonding Commission.

4.) Every year, I'll identify and publish 10% cuts in wasteful spending, starting with my own office. 

 5.) I'll grade every State Government department and agency on their value for money, quality of service to tax-payers and business friendly policies.

6.) I will refuse to certify any budget with typical Hartford accounting gimmicks. 

7.) I'll work to renegotiate the state employee pension plans.

8.) I'll work night and day to re-open Connecticut to business.

9.) I'll take a stand against tolls. No ifs. No buts.
 
I'm running to be your next Republican Comptroller to bring my 40 years experience in running businesses and creating jobs to state government. I'll transform the office of Comptroller into a powerhouse for fiscal responsibility and business expertise, while saying 'NO' to the Hartford career politicians when they demand more spending, taxes and debt.
 
But I need your vote in the Republican Primary on August 14th to do that. I hope I can count on your support. Thank you.
bylines: Mark for Comptroller | J. Kenneth Nowell, Treasurer | Authorized by Mark Greenberg

To hit their goals and try to show some muscle, almost all of the Democrats running for president are jamming their schedules with private fundraising events for wealthy donors. But not Elizabeth. 

She doesn’t host any fundraising events behind closed doors. That gives her more time to talk with voters at public events and work on bold policy ideas — plans that will level the playing field for working people. 

Other candidates are racing to collect big checks from wealthy donors and Wall Street. But we can show the power of grassroots donors coming together as one movement. Will you chip in $3 or whatever you can to help grow our grassroots movement?

If you’ve saved your payment information with ActBlue Express, your donation will be automatically processed:

Chip in $3: http://ewar.ren/v16c
Chip in another amount: http://ewar.ren/h9ly

A healthy environment is vital to Washingtonians’ way of life and the regional economy. But Trump is working to roll back environmental protections to fast-track new construction – regardless of the outcome it has on communities. Sign the petition and tell President Trump: STOP rescinding environmental protections!

ad_creative_body:
🚨BREAKING 🚨 The Democrats of Texas’ State Legislature left the state in order to block Republicans’ Jim Crow-era voter suppression legislation — risking arrest to defend the right to vote. Now, these brave Texas Democrats are in Washington D.C., urging Congress to pass the For the People Act and defend the right to vote from attacks by Republican lawmakers in Texas and across the nation. 

The For the People Act would dramatically expand voting access, eliminate partisan gerrymandering, weaken the influence of dark money in politics, and more. The bill passed in the House, but it’s stalled in the Senate because of GOP attacks on our fundamental right to vote and the Jim Crow filibuster. We need to turn up the pressure to pass this landmark legislation. 

Ayanna and her colleagues understand the importance of expanding the right to vote to make sure everyone — no matter their race, income, gender, or livelihood — can participate in our democracy. The GOP’s attacks on our democracy are only getting more brazen, and we need Ayanna’s leadership more than ever. Can you chip in to help her keep up the fight?

"Ocasio-Cortez said the sort of neighborliness she had seen in Iowa was also at the heart of Sanders’ agenda, and that he stands for a politics of loving thy neighbor.

'To me, that’s what policies like Medicare-for-all are all about,' she said. 'To me, ending police brutality in America is loving thy neighbor. To me, ending a brutal policy of caging children and their parents is about loving thy neighbor. To me, a living wage is loving thy neighbor.'"

ad_creative_body:
Democrats deserve a chance to choose a nominee whose time is not for sale to people who can write big checks. So I’ve made a decision: My presidential primary campaign will be run on the principle of equal access for anybody who joins it -- no fancy receptions or big money fundraisers only with people who can write the big checks. There will be a cost to our approach. In fact, making this decision will ensure that I will be outraised by other candidates in this race. But it’s the right thing to do -- and I know we can do it and win. Will you be a part of this? Chip in today. 

If you’ve saved your payment information with ActBlue Express, your donation will be automatically processed:

ad_creative_body:
In a moment I’m going to ask you to make a donation to my Senate campaign. But I hope you’ll give me a chance to explain why 

We have one of the best chances to flip a Senate seat and help take back the Senate in 2020.

This December, we have a huge goal: 45,000 online donations before our end-of-month deadline. These deadlines can be tough — especially when you are rejecting corporate PAC money.

But I’m committed to running a grassroots campaign built by folks here in Arizona and across the country giving what they can. Chip in and help us get there today.

ad_creative_body:

Cory Booker has been in this race for nine months — he’s spent that time talking to voters, listening to supporters, and figuring out what this country needs. You don’t need to be all in for Cory, but if you want a president who’s in this for the good of the people, donate today.

ad_creative_body:
The night of the Iowa Caucuses, CNN didn’t air Elizabeth’s full speech. But they aired the speeches of other candidates she beat. In New Hampshire, some networks played Vice President Biden’s speech despite the fact that he left the state before polls closed — but not Elizabeth’s even though she outperformed him, again.

Elizabeth knows what it’s like to be counted out early, because it’s happened before. But right now, 55 states and territories have still yet to vote. 98% of delegates are still up for grabs. We can’t count on the media to cover our campaign fairly, so we’re taking our case directly to voters. 

Can Elizabeth count on you? Chip in $2, $20, or whatever you can spare before it’s too late.

ad_creative_body:
Every time Democrats demand investments in our people, the ritual repeats. They always ask, “How are you going to pay for it? Whose taxes are going up?”

Let’s be real. This fight has never been about what we could or couldn’t afford — it’s always been about our priorities. When the House passed a $738 billion military spending bill this month, no one asked how we were going to pay for it. Because in the modern United States, we have unlimited money for bombs, drones, and tanks — but no money to house tens of thousands of homeless children or veterans, or afford food stamps ahead of the holidays.

We need to fundamentally shift Congress by electing new progressive leaders — and AOC raised nearly $300k for those leaders in 2019. Can you help us do even more in 2020 by investing in the movement today?

The House passed a federal spending bill without the Hyde Amendment -- a ban on federal abortion funding -- for the first time in decades. Hyde disproportionately impacts women of color and poor women and undermines Roe v. Wade. 

Diana DeGette knows that reversing Hyde is a matter of racial and economic justice. Add your name now to support ending Hyde once and for all >> https://bit.ly/3zNWONu

ad_creative_body: Members of Congress are encouraged to spend up to five hours a day on “call time” — time solely dedicated to calling up big donors and PACs. That’s more than half of a regular work day! But that’s not how I do things. As the chair of the Congressional Progressive Caucus, and with my recent leadership introducing a wealth tax with Elizabeth Warren, reintroducing Medicare for All, and introducing the College for All Act with Bernie Sanders, I’m keeping my priorities straight: Legislating and fighting for working people. That’s why this month we set a goal of bringing in 3,500 individual donations. Can you chip in today so I can spend more time legislating and less time fundraising?

ad_creative_body:
I'm in Milford, speaking to folks about my Business Plan to hold Hartford accountable as your next Republican Comptroller.

For too long, the State Comptroller has been a rubber stamp for Hartford's reckless spending, taxes and debt. I'm a business leader and a political outsider. I'll re-open Connecticut to business and balance our budgets. And here is my plan to do it:

1.) I'll launch a top-to-bottom audit of all government spending. 

2.) I'll lead by example by refusing a pension.

3.) I'll vote NO against any more excessive borrowing on the State Bonding Commission.

4.) Every year, I'll identify and publish 10% cuts in wasteful spending, starting with my own office. 

 5.) I'll grade every State Government department and agency on their value for money, quality of service to tax-payers and business friendly policies.

6.) I will refuse to certify any budget with typical Hartford accounting gimmicks. 

7.) I'll work to renegotiate the state employee pension plans.

8.) I'll work night and day to re-open Connecticut to business.

9.) I'll take a stand against tolls. No ifs. No buts.
 
I'm running to be your next Republican Comptroller to bring my 40 years experience in running businesses and creating jobs to state government. I'll transform the office of Comptroller into a powerhouse for fiscal responsibility and business expertise, while saying 'NO' to the Hartford career politicians when they demand more spending, taxes and debt.
 
But I need your vote in the Republican Primary on August 14th to do that. I hope I can count on your support. Thank you.
bylines: Mark for Comptroller | J. Kenneth Nowell, Treasurer | Authorized by Mark Greenberg

ad_creative_body:
Actualmente, tenemos una economía y una democracia que favorece a los ricos y bien conectados. Es hora de salvar nuestra democracia. Es hora de construir una economía que funcione para todos y acabar con la corrupción en Washington. Es hora de grandes cambios estructurales. Y sí, tengo un plan para eso. Esto es lo que hará mi administración: Aprobaremos el plan más ambicioso contra la corrupción desde Watergate y acabaremos con el cabildeo tal como lo conocemos.

Regularemos las corporaciones agrícolas, las grandes instituciones bancarias y las compañías tecnológicas. Fortaleceremos nuestros sindicatos y le daremos voz a nuestros trabajadores en las juntas corporativas. Aprobaremos un impuesto de 2 centavos sobre las riquezas de las personas con fortunas de más de $50 millones.  

Y con ese dinero:

Proveeremos cuidado infantil universal y pre-K universal. 

Haremos que la universidad pública sea gratuita y restauraremos nuestras Universidades Históricamente Afroamericanas (HBCUs por sus siglas en inglés). Cancelaremos la deuda por préstamos estudiantiles para el 95% de las personas con este tipo de deuda 

Cuando lidere el Partido Demócrata, lucharemos por una vida mejor para todos los estadounidenses.  Haz clic aquí para aprender más sobre cómo haremos la diferencia para todos los estadounidenses.

Here's what I'd like for you to know about me:

• Christian Conservative Republican
• Wife and Mother of Three
• Business Owner / Job Creator (thousands of jobs in 11 states)
• Political Outsider / Problem Solver
• Georgia Native / UGA Graduate
• 100% Pro-America / 100% Pro-Trump
• 100% Pro-Life / 100% Pro-Gun
• Pass Term Limits on Congress!
• Endorsed by Jim Jordan
• Fighting For the People, Not the Politicians

I’m the strongest conservative in the race. That’s why I’ve been endorsed by Congressman Jim Jordan, House Freedom Fund, Right Women PAC and Law Enforcement Today.

Election Day is Tuesday. Soon, neighbors here in Orange County will know who came out to vote and who stayed home. Who voted to make sure the 1 in 2 of us with a pre-existing condition aren't without healthcare, who stood up for our beaches against big oil special interest money, who stood up for tax fairness and fiscal common sense.
 
The election will be close; every voter will matter. Public records show your polling place is Fire Station 21 located at 1241 Irvine Blvd, Tustin CA 92780. Be a voter anytime between 7a - 8p.
 Vote by mail? Make sure to mail your ballot by Tuesday or drop it off on Tuesday at any polling place or ballot drop box in Orange County.
 
Verify your polling location here: https://electionmapping.ocgov.com/pollfind/index-new.asp?electionabbr=gen2018
 
I hope I can earn your support, and to learn more about me, visit www.facebook.com/pg/katieporteroc/videos 
 We are a community that stands with one another. Show it by being a voter on Tuesday.

ad_creative_body:
When people think of the work of Congress, they often imagine the process of passing bills into law, and that is certainly one part of it. Equally important, however, is the work done in our districts, helping constituents navigate issues with the VA, immigration agencies, State Department, or the IRS, among others. And of course, interacting with our constituents so we understand the local needs and desires of those we represent. 

That’s why it’s important to get home, to talk to voters, and to ensure that we always keep their interests at heart. Here are some my favorites so far from this August:

Having breakfast with the International Alliance of Theatrical Stage Employees (IATSE), Local 80 in Burbank; discussing solutions to homelessness, affordable housing, and humane immigration policy with LA Times Today; speaking with constituents at National Night Out in West Hollywood; hosting a screening and Q&A on how to get dark money out of politics with Dark Money producer/director Kimberly Reed and actress and comedian Kiran Deol; with vintage bobbleheads and friends at the Miracle Mile Democratic Club awards ceremony.

Thank you to all the wonderful constituents who met with me and attended these great local events. Spending time with you is what makes this job so rewarding.

ad_creative_body:
Last week, legislators and the president enacted H.J.Res. 31, fiscal year 2019 (FY19) omnibus spending package that included the Homeland Security Department appropriations compromise as well as six other unfinished FY19 appropriations bills.

The omnibus bill included language to override the president's imposed pay freeze with a 1.9 percent average federal pay raise retroactive to the first pay period of 2019. During this time of economic prosperity and rising private-sector wages, a modest federal pay increase was needed to prevent the federal/private-sector pay gap from further widening. After years of previous pay freezes and meager increases, this common-sense provision circumvents the damage a pay freeze would have inflicted, and will help preserve the federal government's ability to recruit and retain the best and brightest to perform high-level work on the behalf of the American people.

ad_creative_body:
We’ll be honest with you — Wall Street is excited about some of the other Democrats. Other candidates are raising big bucks from big bankers behind closed doors. But Elizabeth’s spent decades fighting to make sure families don’t get cheated by giant financial institutions — because Wall Street shouldn’t be able to write its own rules and get away with crashing the economy.

Some candidates have big-money fundraising down to a science: Swoop into a city, drive to a swanky hotel or hedge fund office, make pleasant chit-chat with the rich and powerful, and scoop up big checks. But not Elizabeth. She doesn’t host any fundraising events behind closed doors. 

We don’t want a government that only looks out for the wealthy and well-connected. We can put power in the hands of the people, where it belongs. And that starts with a grassroots-powered, grassroots-funded campaign for the presidency. Will you chip in $50 now to help us show the power of this grassroots movement before the FEC filing deadline on June 30?

ad_creative_body:
Woo-hoo! We just passed one million donations made to this campaign. That’s one million donations solely from grassroots donors. Zero from closed-door fundraising events. Zero from Washington lobbyists. Zero from corporate PACs, or PACs of any kind. This is a 100% people-powered campaign. 

I had a chance to call Caitlyn, an ESL teacher from Tennessee, to personally thank her for making our one millionth donation! Usually, “call time” on a campaign looks like candidates spending hours a week on the phone asking wealthy donors for big checks. Not on this campaign. I can’t call everyone who makes a donation, but I set aside time in my schedule to call grassroots donors who contribute any amount. 

We can’t stop here. We have to keep this up and hit the next million. If you’re with me, will you chip in $20 or whatever you can to power this movement?

ad_creative_body:
I am honored Fox News included me in the incredible field of Americans who are stepping up to the plate to Save America and Stop Socialism! 

The radical socialist democrat women in Congress haven’t met me yet! 

Unlike them, I LOVE America, our freedoms, Capitalism, and I serve the one true God.

And I’m a Mom fighting for all of our children’s future!

“I'm tired of seeing my president attacked every day,” said Marjorie Greene, a GOP businesswoman and first-time congressional candidate running for an open seat in Georgia’s 14th district. “I'm tired of seeing our future threatened. I'm tired of seeing my children's future extremely threatened, and it’s time to get off the bench and really step up to the plate.”

Like many GOP candidates vying for office this year, Greene takes aim directly at progressive darling Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and her freshman squad and says Congress needs strong conservative women to stand up to “tyrannical socialist Democrats.”

“These are radical women that will not bend. They do not want to work across the aisle. They only want their policies of the Green New Deal, 'Medicare-for-all' and socialism for America,” Greene told Fox News.

“Oftentimes, it takes a woman to put another woman in her place," said Greene, whose family owns a commercial construction company.

Save America, Stop Socialism! #sass

-- Marjorie
www.Greene2020.com/donate

ad_creative_body:
A few days ago the FEC released the fundraising numbers for the candidates running to unseat me. In just the first three months of this year, our Wall Street backed Democratic opponents raised over $1 million against us. I’ve said this from the start: when you speak truth to power, power fights back. They’re coming for me because I call out corrupt Wall Street bailout schemes.

But let’s make one thing clear: we’re going to defeat every single one of them, all without taking a cent of corporate PAC or special interest money. This has always been a people-first movement — and that’s our path to victory. In response, we set a very specific goal of raising $1,124,053 this month — the exact amount our Wall Street backed Democratic opponents raised against us this past quarter. Can we count on you to chip in today?

ad_creative_body:
I have some important news to share, and I wanted you to hear it from me: I am announcing my intention to run for re-election to the United States Senate in 2018. 

Being anti-Trump and anti-Republican is not enough. We need to continue our fight for a progressive agenda that improves the lives of working people throughout our country. We need to keep pushing for Medicare for all, a $15/hour living wage, free college tuition, rebuilding our crumbling infrastructure, fighting climate change and promoting racial, social and environmental justice.

If re-elected, you can be sure that I will continue to fight for a progressive agenda.

Make a donation to my re-election campaign today and help us hit some modest fundraising goals in order to fund this effort. Your donation will go a long way toward ensuring we win in November.

He got involved in the notion that he wanted to do something to advance the cause of the people he grew up with in some meaningful way.

And now, he's doing exactly that for the American people in Congress.

ad_creative_body:
There are less than 2 months before our last official FEC filing of the year and our fundraising numbers will become public. We’ve set an ambitious goal of reaching 438,113 contributions by the end of the year and we’re already over 75% of the way there. Here’s what that means if we can’t meet this goal:
 
So far, we know there are three Republican opponents who are exploring a run against Alexandria — including our opponent from last year who spent over $10 million trying to unseat us. If we don’t appear strong on our FEC report, they’ll use that to lobby high-dollar Republican donors and special interest PACs to invest against us.
 
We can’t let that happen. Too many people are counting on our movement. So before the next few hours are up, can you make a donation of any amount? Even $5 makes a big difference.

ad_creative_body:
Election Day is Tuesday. Soon, our neighbors will know who came out to vote and who stayed home. Who voted to stand with our Veterans and send to Washington one of their own so we do right by them, who listened to our teachers and pushed back on excessive testing in schools, who decided that it was time we said enough to Wall Street and the special interests.
 
The election will be close; every voter will matter. Public records show your polling place is Stafford Senior Center located at 130 S Main Stafford, KS, 67578. Be a voter anytime between 7a - 7p.
 
Verify your polling location here: https://myvoteinfo.voteks.org/VoterView/PollingPlaceSearch.do
 
Twice I signed my name on the dotted line for our country and swore to protect and defend it. Learn why I’m running so I might continue that oath: https://www.facebook.com/pg/votejamesthompson/videos
 
Our Kansas values tell us we stand strong together. Show it by being a voter on Tuesday.

Ayanna didn’t run for office to advance corporate interests — she ran to be a voice for those who have been left out and left behind. Since she was elected in 2018, Ayanna has worked tirelessly to reform our criminal (in)justice system, pass Medicare for All, fight for student debt cancellation, establish a federal job guarantee and implement a $15 minimum wage. 

If you can afford it, please make a contribution right now to help us continue to push for progress and build our movement to create meaningful change.

ad_creative_body:
Democrats deserve a chance to choose a nominee whose time is not for sale to people who can write big checks. So I’ve made a decision: My presidential primary campaign will be run on the principle of equal access for anybody who joins it -- no fancy receptions or big money fundraisers only with people who can write the big checks. There will be a cost to our approach. In fact, making this decision will ensure that I will be outraised by other candidates in this race. Will you be a part of this? Chip in today, and if you get a call from an unlisted number tonight, pick up, because it might be a call from me!

Election Day is Tuesday. Soon, our neighbors will know who came out to vote and who stayed home. Who voted to stand with our Veterans and send to Washington one of their own so we do right by them, who listened to our teachers and pushed back on excessive testing in schools, who decided that it was time we said enough to Wall Street and the special interests.
 
The election will be close; every voter will matter. Public records show your polling place is St Elizabeth Ann Seton located at 645 N 119th St W Wichita, KS, 67235. Be a voter anytime between 7a - 7p.
 
Verify your polling location here: https://myvoteinfo.voteks.org/VoterView/PollingPlaceSearch.do
 
Twice I signed my name on the dotted line for our country and swore to protect and defend it. Learn why I’m running so I might continue that oath: https://www.facebook.com/pg/votejamesthompson/videos
 
Our Kansas values tell us we stand strong together. Show it by being a voter on Tuesday.

ad_creative_body:
I'm about to ask you for a small donation to my 2020 U.S. Senate campaign. Because, if you're like me, you're ready to return power to the people by abolishing the electoral college once and for all. 

The person who wins the most votes should win an election. Period. No president, Democratic or Republican, should EVER be sworn into office after the people vote for someone else. After all, this is supposed to be a democracy! 

Standing in the way? Mitch McConnell and an obstructionist Senate. That's where YOU come in.

I'm running for the U.S. Senate in Oregon because we must get the Senate working again so we can get power back to the people -- instead of having it stuck with the elite, the few elected officials in the Senate who are determined to hold onto power.

If we're ever going to abolish the electoral college, or do anything else that puts the needs of the American people ahead of the power and profits of the wealthiest and giant corporations, we must take back the Senate and be ready with a strong, people-first vision.

Together, we can get this done.  Join the fight by donating to my campaign today.

In my many years as a public servant here in Ohio, I’ve been listening and hearing folks’ firsthand struggles during one of the most challenging times in our country’s history. It’s critical that we continue to push for more so we can improve the conditions of people’s lives. Every contribution helps ensure this people-powered movement can get to Congress and fight for a more progressive future.

ad_creative_body: Making sure our nation’s veterans have access to great health care has always been a top priority of mine. That is why I introduced my Veterans Adult Day Health Care bill, to expand health care options for our disabled vets. I was very excited to announce that my proposal was passed and signed into law earlier this year. Adult Day Health Care is available at the Long Island State Veterans Home in Stony Brook and now can be provided at no cost to severely disabled veterans thanks to my bill. It is my greatest honor to secure many important victories for our nation's heroes willing to sacrifice everything in defense of our freedoms and liberties.

ad_creative_body:
I'm in Waterbury, speaking to folks about my Business Plan to hold Hartford accountable as your next Republican Comptroller.

For too long, the State Comptroller has been a rubber stamp for Hartford's reckless spending, taxes and debt. I'm a business leader and a political outsider. I'll re-open Connecticut to business and balance our budgets. And here is my plan to do it:

1.) I'll launch a top-to-bottom audit of all government spending. 

2.) I'll lead by example by refusing a pension.

3.) I'll vote NO against any more excessive borrowing on the State Bonding Commission.

4.) Every year, I'll identify and publish 10% cuts in wasteful spending, starting with my own office. 

 5.) I'll grade every State Government department and agency on their value for money, quality of service to tax-payers and business friendly policies.

6.) I will refuse to certify any budget with typical Hartford accounting gimmicks. 

7.) I'll work to renegotiate the state employee pension plans.

8.) I'll work night and day to re-open Connecticut to business.

9.) I'll take a stand against tolls. No ifs. No buts.
 
I'm running to be your next Republican Comptroller to bring my 40 years experience in running businesses and creating jobs to state government. I'll transform the office of Comptroller into a powerhouse for fiscal responsibility and business expertise, while saying 'NO' to the Hartford career politicians when they demand more spending, taxes and debt.
 
But I need your vote in the Republican Primary on August 14th to do that. I hope I can count on your support. Thank you.
bylines: Mark for Comptroller | J. Kenneth Nowell, Treasurer | Authorized by Mark Greenberg

This Wednesday at midnight we have a huge milestone for the campaign. It’ll be the very first official FEC quarterly fundraising deadline of the 2022 election cycle.
 
That means we’ll submit a public report to the FEC about how much we’ve raised so far this year. This report is scrutinized heavily, so it’s important for us to be able to post strong numbers. Right now we’re 86% of the way toward our goal with $2,575,964 raised of $3,000,000.
 
There’s a lot coming up — from big legislative pushes around infrastructure to a redistricting fight that will change the boundaries of New York’s congressional districts. That’s why we’re writing today asking for your support before the FEC report is due.
 
If you can afford it, please rush a contribution to our campaign. We know it’s a lot to ask, but we know we can make our goal with your support. We’re already 86% of the way there now. Can you help us in the final stretch?

ad_creative_body:
Today, on #InternationalWomensDay, I’m celebrating all of the women making change in this world. In 2018, we elected more women to Congress than ever before, including my good friend and colleague from Kansas, Representative Sharice Davids. I’m dedicated to supporting women, uplifting women, and electing more women to all levels of office. 

I’m honored to have strong women leading my organization and my campaign team is currently 100% #poweredbywomen. As Chair of one of the oldest committees in Congress, the Transportation and Infrastructure Committee, I was humbled to appoint the first *ever* woman Chief of Staff to the committee in our nation’s history. 

International Women’s Day is a time to recognize that we must achieve equality for women. I’m dedicated to defending a woman’s right to choose, and I am proud to be the only candidate in my race endorsed by both Planned Parenthood PAC and NARAL Pro-Choice Oregon. I will continue to fight for paid family leave, to close the gender wage gap, and to always stand against sexual harassment and discrimination in the workplace. I’m proud to have authored the Stop Sexual Assault and Harassment in Transportation Act to improve safety and ensure accountability for transportation workers and the traveling public. 

Join me today (and every day) in celebrating women and honoring their contributions to history, endurance against hate and bigotry, and strength to keep us moving to a better future.

ad_creative_body:
Nancy Pelosi is back from Hawaii, but the government is still not running. 

The border remains weak, illicit drugs still flow into the country, and America seeks answers. 

I spent time last week holding public forums in Poplar Bluff and Cuba Missouri, and I heard firsthand how frustrated Missourians are at the disconnect in Washington. It simply does not compute for them, nor for me, how the Speaker can be so quick to play the blame game and then catch a flight to a resort. 

At our townhalls we had great conversations about securing the border, building a wall, as well as government welfare programs, education, our military, and our farmlands.

Missourians know that you buckle down during hard times. You stick it out. You don’t abandon the government you’ve sworn to serve. More of our leaders should spend time talking to those they are supposed to represent before debating and voting on major issues like our border and our government.

America is a democracy. We deserve leaders that act like it.

The election will be close; every voter will matter. Public records show your polling place is Atria Golden Creek located at 33 Creek Rd, Irvine CA 92604. Be a voter anytime between 7a - 8p.
 Vote by mail? Make sure to mail your ballot by Tuesday or drop it off on Tuesday at any polling place or ballot drop box in Orange County.
 
Verify your polling location here: https://electionmapping.ocgov.com/pollfind/index-new.asp?electionabbr=gen2018
 
I hope I can earn your support, and to learn more about me, visit www.facebook.com/pg/katieporteroc/videos

"I am one of eight children born to migrant workers in my hometown of Laredo, Texas. From the age of four years old, I went with my parents out in the fields. I washed dishes to pay for my education, and I went on to dedicate my life to public service. 

Here in America, I believe that family values, education, and hard work can open doors to a better life. They certainly did for me. All Americans deserve those same opportunities to build a better life for themselves. That’s why I’m running for re-election. I hope you’ll join me on this journey. 
"

Necesitamos la voz de Alexandria en el Congreso para luchar por las familias de Queens y el Bronx. Vota por AOC este 23 de junio.

We fought hard to get where we are. People like you spoke out. Mobilized. Voted. Now, our Democratic majorities in Congress are helping Joe Biden and Kamala Harris unleash a bold agenda for the American people.

But I’ve got to be honest with you about where things stand in Florida: Donald Trump has made Mar-a-Lago the de facto headquarters of the Republican Party – and the GOP is unleashing massive sums of money to keep their far-right members in power. 

That’s why I need grassroots activists like you to help me defeat this GOP onslaught – so Democrats can keep doing what’s right for the American people. But I’m falling $1,284 short of our midnight fundraising goal and won’t get there without your support. Will you donate now to defeat the GOP in Florida?

ad_creative_body:
In a moment, I’m going to ask you to pledge to vote in this election, but first I want to take a moment to explain why this is so important.
 
Patriotism is love of country. But you can’t love your country without loving your countrymen and countrywomen. We don’t always have to agree, but we must empower each other, we must find common ground, we must build bridges across our differences to pursue the common good. That’s what democracy is all about: one person, one vote, regardless of background or opinion. I am a patriot -- and I will fight to my last breath to defend our democracy. It’s how we get things done and create lasting change, bending the arc of history toward justice.
 
That’s why we need to pass the John Lewis Voting Rights Act. Our right to vote is under daily attack from a President trying to muddy the waters on what a free and fair election looks like. We cannot let that happen.
 
We have an opportunity, in a matter of weeks, to send a strong message that we will not accept attacks on our democracy. We need a huge turnout in races up and down the ballot to say enough is enough. 
 
So, will you take a second today to pledge to vote? The future of our democracy is at stake.

ad_creative_body: Georgetown University’s School of Public Policy rated me as being in the top 10% in the Congress for my bipartisanship. We've got to work together if we want to get the job done for Alaska. I've been lucky enough to serve the great people of Alaska for 22 terms and during that time I've been able work with anyone and everyone to get bills passed and signed into law. Whether it was working to get the Trans-Alaska Pipeline or the 200 mile territorial limit, or more recently with getting ANWR across the finish line - I'll continue working hard for Alaskans.

In Washington State, we already have universal, postage-paid mail-in voting. But many states don't. And now, President Trump is thwarting efforts to expand mail-in voting. 

We can't play politics with people's health. Add your name to join Dr. Kim Schrier in calling for universal mail-in voting to protect voters' rights and health >> https://bit.ly/35jNkvd

ad_creative_body:
Monday is our last day to hit our End of Quarter fundraising goals. Meeting our goals will mean we’re able to grow this movement, increase the number of states we’re organizing in, and share more big plans to get our country working for working people. 

Other candidates are racing to be able to announce big numbers thanks to big checks from wealthy donors and Wall Street. Even though the pressure is high, you won’t see Elizabeth jetting around the country to host swanky fundraisers with wealthy donors behind closed doors. 

We can show the power of grassroots donors coming together as one movement. We’re close to our target thanks to thousands of grassroots donors, but we need your help to cross the finish line. That’s why we’ve set a goal of 190 donors from California before midnight on Monday. Chip in now to help power this grassroots movement.

ad_creative_body: In an 1867 speech, abolitionist Frederick Douglass described self-governance as succinctly as anyone could - "A man's rights rest in three boxes: the ballot box, the jury box, and the cartridge box." Only we the people are responsible for the nation we pass along to our children and grandchildren. The government we have is the government we allow to exist. That’s why I fight for smaller government, and more individual freedom.

Join us and together we can lift our entire island communities up >>>

ad_creative_body:
Election Day is Tuesday. Soon, our neighbors will know who came out to vote and who stayed home. Who voted to stand with our Veterans and send to Washington one of their own so we do right by them, who listened to our teachers and pushed back on excessive testing in schools, who decided that it was time we said enough to Wall Street and the special interests.
 
The election will be close; every voter will matter. Public records show your polling place is Kingman Expo Center located at 110 W First Ave Kingman, KS, 67068. Be a voter anytime between 7a - 7p.
 
Verify your polling location here: https://myvoteinfo.voteks.org/VoterView/PollingPlaceSearch.do
 
Twice I signed my name on the dotted line for our country and swore to protect and defend it. Learn why I’m running so I might continue that oath: https://www.facebook.com/pg/votejamesthompson/videos
 
Our Kansas values tell us we stand strong together. Show it by being a voter on Tuesday.

ad_creative_body: #TBT: On the morning of Nov. 4th, 2014, I went to the Mastic Beach Fire Department with my family to cast my vote to improve the representation of our great Congressional District. Every minute of every day since has been the highest privilege to be your voice in our nation’s capital to protect our Republic from threats inside and out that seek to silence us. We will never rest, especially as those threats continue to exist to pursue policies equally flawed inside and out. This nation is worth fighting for and protecting at any and all costs.

We’re going to cover the walls of Warren HQ in Boston with the names of supporters who make this grassroots movement possible. Our new Grassroots Donor Wall will be a constant reminder of what —and who— our campaign is fighting for.

Chip in anything today to add your name to our Grassroots Donor Wall.

Thanks to the efforts of President Trump and Congressman Walden, Oregon will receive within the next few weeks somewhere around $1.2 billion dollars from the federal government to spend as it decides.  These funds must be used to support ALL Oregonians, not just Portland.  

Today, I sent a letter to Governor Kate Brown recommending a handful of things she can do to support our essential workers, our students and our local businesses. Our rural communities and Oregon’s future depends on it. 

If you agree with my recommendations and want Governor Brown to be a leader for ALL of Oregon, then add your name to the letter.

ad_creative_body:
We need emergency legislation to ensure that the 2020 election is accessible to every single American who wants to vote by mail.

We don't know what path the coronavirus outbreak will take. We have to ensure that the 2020 election happens, happens safely, and includes every eligible voter.

We simply cannot require millions of Americans — including medical first responders and the sick — to stand in long lines waiting to vote.

Sign my petition to demand national vote-by-mail in 2020.

ad_creative_body:
Every day, the rhetoric from my fellow candidates seems to get more and more polarizing.

Our nation is more bitterly divided now than it’s ever been in my lifetime. It’s sickening.

As the Governor of Colorado, a purple state, I learned how to solve this problem: 

Bring opposing viewpoints together, to talk things over and reach a compromise. 

It’s really that simple.

Working together, we passed meaningful reforms to:

Curb climate change.
Improve our communities’ relationships with police.
Institute common sense gun laws.
Create a thriving economy.
Get healthcare coverage for 95% of the population.

Now, Colorado is a thriving state. Our cities are often ranked among the top places to live in America.

It is possible to make real progress when we work together, instead of against one another.

We need 130,000 donors to get to the next round of the debates this fall. Just $1 will help us reach our goal.

Chip in a dollar, or whatever you can, to help us unite our divided nation:

ad_creative_body:
"The Professional Firefighters of Marion County are pleased to extend to our full endorsement of Kat Cammack’s candidacy for Florida’s 3rd Congressional District.

As the wife of a local first responder, her passionate advocacy of first responders and their families is clear. The recent Covid-19 outbreak clearly demonstrates that first responders’ duty to serve and protect our citizens puts us and our families at immediate risk. First responders accept the risks associated with servicing our communities and only ask of our elected officials that they support us to that end. Kat has shown throughout your career of public service that you do.

Her co-founding of the GRIT Foundation is one example of her commitment to first responders. The GRIT Foundation’s sole purpose is to generate community-based support for local first responders and our hometown heroes. This support cannot be understated during the crisis we currently face. 

Kat served for nearly a decade as Congressman Ted Yoho’s Deputy Chief of Staff. In that capacity, she navigated the federal government and collaborated with federal agencies in advocacy of first responders’ needs. This has not gone unnoticed by us in Marion County, Florida.

Because of her support of the citizens of Marion County and the first responders who have sworn to protect them, the Professional Firefighters of Marion County offer her any support you need to ensure the success of her candidacy and her election to Florida’s 3rd Congressional District."

- Daniel D. Garcia, President of the Professional Firefighters of Marion County, Local 3169

ad_creative_body:
Halloween is here, and it’s kind of appropriate this holiday falls near Election Day. That’s because it’s worth considering the scary future the Left promises if they manage to take Congress.

Just consider the pledges Nancy Pelosi has made if she regains the Speaker’s chair. She has vowed to raise taxes and roll back our historic tax reforms. She also recently said she will launch a series of gun-control measures to curb our Constitutional 2nd Amendment rights. And then there are the Left’s plans to abolish ICE and harbor illegal aliens.

Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer, who hopes to change his title to Majority Leader come January, has vowed to ramp up the obstruction against anything the Trump administration proposes. And he has made clear how critical it is to the Left that they not confirm Administration nominees, particularly for the federal judiciary.

Those are frightening possibilities, to be sure. 

And let’s not forget the biggest specter haunting this election – the threat of impeachment by those who still can’t get over having lost the 2016 election. 

The good news is that if we work hard and get out the votes on Nov. 6, we can ensure that these leftist scares and threats remain just a nightmare, and not a reality, for the American people.

But Elizabeth’s spent decades fighting to make sure families don’t get cheated by giant financial institutions — because Wall Street shouldn’t be able to write its own rules and get away with crashing the economy.

Some candidates have big-money fundraising down to a science: Swoop into a city, drive to a swanky hotel or hedge fund office, make pleasant chit-chat with the rich and powerful, and scoop up big checks. But not Elizabeth. She doesn’t host any fundraising events behind closed doors. 

We don’t want a government that only looks out for the wealthy and well-connected. We can put power in the hands of the people, where it belongs. And that starts with a grassroots-powered, grassroots-funded campaign for the presidency. Will you chip in now to help us show the power of this grassroots movement?

I’m pleased to announce that I will NOT be gathering signatures for my 2020 re-election.

To protect our conservative agenda -- and to defeat Congressional Democrats’ agenda of the Green New Deal, open borders, and infanticide – will you stand with me by contributing today, before the deadline hits?

Thank you for your support.

Ted

We're not going to sugarcoat this: We're days away from the end of the year, and we're short of where we need to be to hit our fundraising goals.

In just over a week, we'll wrap the last FEC fundraising report that will become public before voting begins. A lot of people are waiting to see our final FEC report of the year so that they can characterize the strength that this grassroots movement is bringing into 2020 — so it’s powerfully important for us to close out the year strong, and we can’t do that without your help.

What you give today is going to power the growth of this grassroots movement. Will you make a donation today, of any amount, and help build this campaign as we approach our final critical FEC deadline of the year?

We can show the power of grassroots donors coming together as one movement on December 31. Will you chip in $5, $20 or whatever you can before the end of the year?

If you’ve saved your payment information with ActBlue Express, your donation will be automatically processed:

Chip in $5: https://ewar.ren/kpvn
Chip in $10: https://ewar.ren/zynt
Chip in $20: https://ewar.ren/rzk6
Chip in $50: https://ewar.ren/x8fx

Join her in demanding Congress pass legislation to end robocalls once and for all. Add your name now >> https://bit.ly/2q1JwOH

ad_creative_body:
The Bronx and Westchester are at the epicenter of the coronavirus crisis and we need a leader who's in touch with the pain of our communities right now.

Jamaal Bowman is a Democrat running for Congress who has served our communities as a principal of an award-winning public school in the Bronx for ten years.

Bowman lives in Yonkers and has been rooted in the communities that this crisis has hit the hardest. Nearly 40 percent of Black and Latino Americans have already missed a rent or utility bill due to the pandemic. That’s why Bowman is fighting to:
- Keep workers on payroll by providing grants to businesses
- Expand Medicare to cover all coronavirus care
- Suspend rent and mortgage payments
- Provide emergency monthly cash assistance of $2,000 for every American

We’ve had the same Congressman representing us for 31 years and things aren’t getting better for most of us. This is the worst crisis since the Great Depression and people don’t even know where their Congressman is. It feels like he’s taking us for granted.

After 31 years of the same representation, it’s time for a change. Choose Jamaal on your absentee ballot before June 23 to make your voice heard.

We took a look at our fundraising this morning, and we were blown away by the response we received yesterday. We are now only $11,467 short of where we need to be to stay on track for October. It is essential to our campaign operations that we meet our monthly goals — we know from years of organizing and working to build progressive power that taking off-years is how elections are lost.

Traditionally, campaigns start voter outreach a few months before the election. We do things differently. 

We organize 365 days a year because we know that’s what’s required to build power to take on special interests and win the progressive reforms we need — like raising the minimum wage, cancelling student debt, reimagining our immigration system, and more. It’s why we host weekly Green New Deal phone banks, coordinate disaster relief efforts, and work to support progressive candidates like India Walton.
 
We have 12 hours to make up the difference to stay on track for October. Can you chip in $5 or $10 today to close the gap?

ad_creative_body:
Right now, Democrats running for president are staring down the FEC fundraising deadline on June 30. To hit their goals and try to show some muscle, almost all of the other candidates are jamming their schedules with private fundraising events for wealthy donors. But not Elizabeth. 

She doesn’t host any fundraising events behind closed doors. That gives her more time to talk with voters at public events and work on bold policy ideas — plans that will level the playing field for working people. 

Next month, all of the candidates will announce how much money they’ve raised in the second quarter of 2019, up through the June 30 deadline. Other candidates are racing to be able to announce big numbers thanks to big checks from wealthy donors and Wall Street— and give reporters and pundits sticker shock. But we can show the power of grassroots donors coming together as one movement. Will you chip in $10 or whatever you can to help grow our grassroots movement?

ad_creative_body:
Election Day is Tuesday. Soon, neighbors here in Orange County will know who came out to vote and who stayed home. Who voted to make sure the 1 in 2 of us with a pre-existing condition aren't without healthcare, who stood up for our beaches against big oil special interest money, who stood up for tax fairness and fiscal common sense.
 
The election will be close; every voter will matter. Public records show your polling place is Stone Residence located at 21641 Cabrosa, Mission Viejo CA 92691. Be a voter anytime between 7a - 8p.
 Vote by mail? Make sure to mail your ballot by Tuesday or drop it off on Tuesday at any polling place or ballot drop box in Orange County.
 
Verify your polling location here: https://electionmapping.ocgov.com/pollfind/index-new.asp?electionabbr=gen2018
 
I hope I can earn your support, and to learn more about me, visit www.facebook.com/pg/katieporteroc/videos 
 We are a community that stands with one another. Show it by being a voter on Tuesday.

ad_creative_body:
This election is not over yet. 

Our Republican opponent just launched a new television ad campaign attacking AOC, our platform, and the community that we’re fighting for. That’s what we’re up against when our opponent takes in cash from Trump donors, Wall Street, and corporate America. 

Our opponent is trying to “help retire AOC” because he understands what it means if AOC wins another term in Congress. Our movement has already inspired diverse, working-class candidates across the country to run for office. In two short years, Alexandria has already pushed the needle on critical progressive issues in the Democratic Party. 

Republicans understand that they’re losing the fight for the hearts and minds of working people in this country. But instead of fighting to better their lives, they’re throwing millions of dollars into an attempt to unseat our movement. We’re not going to let that happen. 

We set a very specific goal of raising $1,000,958 this month — the exact amount of cash on hand they have to spend against us. We’re 47% of our way to this goal. Can you chip in today help us reach our goal?

ad_creative_body:
We’ll be honest with you — Wall Street is excited about some of the other Democrats. Other candidates are raising big bucks from big bankers behind closed doors. But Elizabeth’s spent decades fighting to make sure families don’t get cheated by giant financial institutions — because Wall Street shouldn’t be able to write its own rules and get away with crashing the economy.

Some candidates have big-money fundraising down to a science: Swoop into a city, drive to a swanky hotel or hedge fund office, make pleasant chit-chat with the rich and powerful, and scoop up big checks. But not Elizabeth. She doesn’t host any fundraising events behind closed doors. 

We don’t want a government that only looks out for the wealthy and well-connected. We can put power in the hands of the people, where it belongs. And that starts with a grassroots-powered, grassroots-funded campaign for the presidency. Will you chip in $3 now to help us show the power of this grassroots movement?

If you’ve saved your payment information with ActBlue Express, your donation will be automatically processed:

Chip in $3: http://ewar.ren/0w1
Chip in another amount: http://ewar.ren/ykl

Happy back to school & info about getting ready to vote! Here are the two most important things you can do now to get ready:
1. Register to VOTE and check your registration at www.NMvote.org.
2. Make a PLAN
-OPTION A. VOTE BY MAIL: If you plan to vote by mail, you MUST request a ballot. You can do so by contacting the County Clerk’s office, downloading the form online and mailing it back now, or filling out the request form the Clerk will send on Sept 14th!  https://www.bernco.gov/clerk/absentee-voting.aspx
-OPTION B. VOTE IN PERSON: If you plan to vote in person, please consider voting early between Oct 17-31.  Pick a day and put it on your calendar and know when and where you plan to vote! Info on early voting here! https://www.bernco.gov/clerk/early-voting-locations.aspx

If you have ANY questions at all—shoot me a message or call any time!  (505) 750-7079.  

Thanks everyone!  Let’s do this!!

Our campaign is helping elect progressives across the country who will fight for long-term, systemic solutions, like Medicare For All, a federal jobs guarantee, and an end to mass incarceration.
